This paper deals with a data structure for the two-dimensional sorted range reporting problem, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and data structures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves geometric concepts and algorithms, which suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as another likely category. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the space and query time complexity of the data structure, which could fall under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper proposes an improvement to a recent result, which could also fall under cs.AL (Algorithms and Complexity).
